Interface Summary
Declaration<E extends Declaration<E,P,S,D>,P extends DeclarationContainer,S extends Signature,D extends Declaration> A declaration introduces an element that can be referenced from other parts of the code.
DeclarationContainer<E extends DeclarationContainer,P extends Element> A general interface for elements that contain declarations.
Definition<E extends Definition<E,P,S,F>,P extends DeclarationContainer,S extends Signature,F extends Declaration> A definition is a declaration that needs a definition.
